            . I have a number of articles pawned with me. I cannot be certain of the prisoner's person.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270405-229-person1277">
                  PETER 
                  BOSTON
               <interp inst="t18270405-229-person1277" type="surname" value="BOSTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-229-person1277" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-229-person1277" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer, and took the prisoner in charge; he conducted himself in a very proper manner.</p>
               <p>The prisoner, in a long address to the Court, stated that he had undergone the greatest deprivation, for want of food, having five children, and had taken these things to supply a craving appetite, and had given every information to lead to the recovery of the property, and expressed his sincere contrition.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 44.</p>
